<br>
Stolen from here or Safehouse, I ferget:<br>
<br>
..___________.. <br>
/..........1........\ <br>
|.....................| <br>
|2.........O.......3| <br>
|.....................| <br>
|.....................| <br>
.\__.............__/. <br>
.....|.........|..... <br>
.....|.........|..... <br>
.....|.........|..... <br>
.....|.........|.....<br>
.....|.........|..... <br>
.....|.........|..... <br>
.....|....4....|.....<br>
.....|.D..D..D.|.....<br>
<br>
O = ring <br>
1-4 = spawn points <br>
D = Deathtouch mobs restricting retreat <br>
<br>
Pre-Ring information:<br>
1) Set up camp on the bridge. Stay in the middle area. Buff up properly. <br>
2) When everyone is ready, start the ring.<br>
3) ONLY one monk goes into the ring. This is the Ring Trigger (RT)<br>
4) RT stays standing until mobs spawn. RT feigns once mobs spawn.<br>
        4a) If the RT dies, a Backup Ring Trigger takes his place until the RT is back.<br>
        4b) RT stays grouped with a shaman to heal and a small enchanter team.<br>
        4c) The RT and BRT should use hotkeys to alert the guild to every SPAWN and SPLIT.<br>
5) Once the ring is clear of mobs, the RT stands again and repeats. <br>
6) Before every boss, and sometimes after as well, a CH/Gain Mana will cast on raid.        <br>
<br>
Wave #1: 1 wurm approaches from behind, 2 drakes spawn in ring<br>
.........RAMPAGING hatchlings will spawn randomly in the ring<br>
<br>
Wave #2: one Templar (FLURRY DRAKE) spawns in the ring<br>
.........RAMPAGING hatchlings will spawn randomly in the ring<br>
<br>
Wave #3: two wurms come from behind and two drakes spawn in the ring<br>
.........upon any deaths, a carrion drake will spawn<br>
<br>
<br>
BOSS #1: Zruk the Lifestealer spawns (4) <br>
.........every time someone dies, a carrion drake spawns (1) <br>
<br>
Wave #5: two wurms come from behind, two drakes spawn in the ring<br>
.........RAMPAGING hatchlings randomly spawn in the ring<br>
<br>
Wave #6: two split drakes spawn (2 and 4) <br>
.........whenever a drake is killed, more spawn in the ring<br>
.........11 each splitter, 22 drakes total (offtank one)<br>
<br>
Wave #7: three templars (FLURRY DRAKES) spawn in the ring, one behind <br>
.........AE Tash the three in the ring<br>
<br>
BOSS #2: Rathek the Tigerclaw spawns in ring with a RAMPAGING racnar pet<br>
<br>
Wave #9: five destroyers spawn, four in the ring and one from behind<br>
.........the destroyers proc a knockback spell<br>
<br>
Wave #10: two templars (FLURRY DRAKES) spawn in the ring<br>
..........AE Tash<br>
<br>
Wave #11: one templar and two destroyers spawn in the ring<br>
..........AE Tash<br>
<br>
BOSS #3: Vethrol the Skycaller spawns in the ring<br>
.........procs 500DD + Whirl till you Hurl randomly<br>
<br>
Wave #13: three templars (FLURRY DRAKES) spawn in the ring<br>
..........AE Tash<br>
<br>
Wave #14: three wardens spawn in the ring<br>
..........3 each splitter, 9 drakes total<br>
<br>
Wave #15: two wardens spawn in the ring<br>
..........11 each splitter, 22 drakes total (off tank one)<br>
<br>
BOSS #4: The Herald of Vulak'Aerr spawns in the ring<br>
.........must be in melee range to cast on<br>
.........doesn't hit hard but he does he fast<br>
<br>
BOSS #5: Vulak'Aerr spawns (1)<br>
.........Vulak'Aerr is rooted, so debuffs can be done before engaging<br>
.........his AE is now disease based and can be cured<br>
<br>
The first three waves are very straight forward and simple. These should be used to practice assisting and killing drakes in a certain order. <br>
<br>
Once WAVE 4 starts, things start to get serious. Two warders spawn, which result in a total of TWENTY TWO drakes when all is said and done. Even after doing a great job of assisting and tanking adds, we ended up getting shafted int he end when Templars spawned during the second chain cycle. It is my recommendation to keep the second chain trigger tanked fur the duration of the Ring Event or until we get spare time to kill it.<br>
<br>
<br>
When WAVE 5 starts, the ring trigger, whom is in the room alone, will DA tank the templars while an enchanter will Wind of Tashania them. Cutting this debuff out immediately at the start will let our shamans malo + slow the FLURRY drakes with less resists, saving a lot of lives and getting the mobs slowed faster. This will be set up for every wave from this point on.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saperthebigcushion>Saper The Big Cushion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 4:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Vulak Ring</span><hr size=1> nice info, thanks<br>
